  "prompt": "What is the average number of followers per user on Instagram",
  "response": "As of my last update, the average number of followers per user on Instagram can fluctuate widely depending on various factors, including user demographics and engagement. On average, estimates have suggested that Instagram users tend to have anywhere from 150 to 200 followers; however, this figure can vary greatly. \n\nInfluencers and brands often have significantly higher follower counts, while many casual users may have fewer. Instagram's user base also includes a large number of accounts with very few or even no followers. \n\nFor the most current statistics, you might consider checking recent studies or reports from social media analytics companies, as these numbers change frequently.",
